<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1612,1963]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1721,1747]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from single female specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1130,1721,1747]" name="Jamaica" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
and subsequently reported from other localities. It is probable that 
<taxonomicName box="[598,697,1757,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Megamelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cultus">
<emphasis box="[598,697,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. cultus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is synonymous with some other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1971" box="[1186,1314,1757,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1186,1314,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Chionomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, because the 
<typeStatus box="[291,389,1793,1819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
is female (with no definitively associated males), we have found no certain method to confidently associate it with any other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1971" box="[554,682,1829,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,682,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Chionomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, and we are reluctant to speculate especially given that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Megamelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cultus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. cultus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be the senior name. The following species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1971" box="[820,948,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[820,948,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Chionomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1161,1256,1865,1891]" name="Jamaica" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muir &amp; Giffard" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1267,1396,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="havanae">
<emphasis box="[1267,1396,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. havanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muir &amp; Giffard" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balboae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. balboae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muir" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[257,409,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Syndelphax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dissapatus">
<emphasis box="[257,409,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. dissapatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Van Duzee" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[425,541,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puellus">
<emphasis box="[425,541,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. puellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Muir" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[556,652,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenae">
<emphasis box="[556,652,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. tenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Crawford" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[709,844,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis box="[709,844,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As the 
<typeStatus box="[941,1039,1901,1927]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
is a female, subsequently reported localities are doubtful.
</paragraph>
